<task id="019" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>ComposerActionBar sub-component — Send / Save Draft / Cancel + view-mode actions</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>011</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Action bar component; no architecture decisions; uses Fluent v9 button primitives. STANDARD covers it.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-01, FR-10</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build `<ComposerActionBar />` at `subcomponents/ComposerActionBar.tsx`. Renders the action buttons appropriate for the current `mode`. Hidden entirely when `mount='inline'` (wizard frame owns navigation per NFR-03).

    Per-mode action sets:
    - `compose`: Send (primary), Save Draft, Cancel
    - `view`: Edit, Reply, Forward, Close (no Send)
    - `reply`: Send (primary), Save Draft, Cancel
    - `forward`: Send (primary), Save Draft, Cancel
    - `draft`: Send (primary), Save Draft (re-saves), Discard, Close

    Props:
    - `mode: EmailComposerMode`
    - `mount: EmailComposerMount` (used only to decide whether to render at all)
    - `isSending: boolean` (disables Send + shows spinner)
    - `isDirty: boolean` (enables Save Draft only when dirty)
    - `onSend, onSaveDraft, onCancel, onEdit, onReply, onForward, onClose, onDiscard` callbacks (engine wires them to reducer actions / imperative handle methods)

    Layout: `page` mount uses bottom-right primary-action chrome; `dialog` mount uses dialog footer chrome. Both visually similar — `mount` prop drives spacing tokens but action set is the same.

    Render NOTHING when `mount === 'inline'` (return `null`).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer; Fluent v9 Button + Toolbar primitives; familiar with the conditional-render-by-mode pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `<ComposerActionBar />` compiles + lint-clean. All 5 modes render the correct action sets. `mount='inline'` returns null. Send disabled when `isSending`. Save Draft disabled when `!isDirty`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per NFR-03 mount variants: inline = wizard owns nav; dialog/page = composer owns. ActionBar is the locus of this distinction.

      Per FR-10: view mode shows Edit/Reply/Forward/Close instead of Send/Cancel — composer "knows" it's read-only.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/ComposerActionBar.tsx (NEW)</file>
